          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-07 20:37:09" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:διασπείρω&lt;SDBG:διασπείρω:000000&gt;} ‘to scatter,’ {D:15.136}) the region or area in which persons have been scattered (particularly a reference to the nation of Israel which had been scattered throughout the ancient world)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>region in which people are scattered</Gloss>
                <Gloss>diaspora</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>For the most part, the phrase ταῖς δώδεκα φυλαῖς in {S:05900100100028} has been interpreted as a reference to believers in Christ. In translating, one may render the term διασπορά as ‘in all the regions where they have been scattered,’ thus rendering this expression in {S:05900100100028} as ‘greetings to all of God’s people in all of the regions in which they have been scattered.’</Comments>
